                <fr:route>/todo-0005/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Intuition: Borel \sigma -algebra">Intuition: Borel <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Intuition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
The <fr:link href="/gtop-000K/" title="Borel \sigma -algebra" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000K/" display-uri="gtop-000K" type="local">Borel <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</fr:link> is what you get by starting from the <fr:link href="/gtop-0005/" title="Open Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0005/" display-uri="gtop-0005" type="local">open sets</fr:link> and asking: what is the smallest <fr:link href="/gtop-000M/" title="\sigma -algebra" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000M/" display-uri="gtop-000M" type="local"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</fr:link> containing all of them?
</html:p>
                <html:p>
The <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topology</fr:link> decides what is open. The Borel <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra is the cheapest way to turn that into something you can measure. You take the open sets and "complete" them: add all <fr:link href="/gtop-0006/" title="Closed Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0006/" display-uri="gtop-0006" type="local">closed</fr:link> sets (complements), countable intersections of open sets (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G_\delta ]]></fr:tex> sets), countable unions of closed sets (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_\sigma ]]></fr:tex> sets), and so on.
</html:p>
                <html:p>
Why minimal? A bigger <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra means more sets to measure, which is harder to do consistently. The Borel <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra includes exactly the sets that the topology forces you to measure — nothing more.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
