            <fr:route>/gtop-000M/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="\sigma -algebra"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
A <html:strong><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</html:strong> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a collection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F} \subseteq  \mathcal {P}(X)]]></fr:tex> of subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> satisfying:
</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \in  \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \in  \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \setminus  A \in  \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> (closed under complements).</html:li>
<html:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\left \{ A_n \right \}_{n=1}^{\infty } \subseteq  \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcup _{n=1}^{\infty } A_n \in  \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> (closed under countable unions).</html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p>
The pair <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, \mathcal {F})]]></fr:tex> is called a <html:strong>measurable space</html:strong>, and the members of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> are called <html:strong>measurable sets</html:strong>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
